{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17628541","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17628541"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:57:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:57:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17224"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17224","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17224"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.04,0.08,0,0.84]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9914"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71643"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9914","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9914"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17224"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57139"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"6942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10047"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23253"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23259"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71643"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the normal defecation reflex?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Rectal distension triggers immediate faecal expulsion","Internal anal sphincter remains contracted throughout defecation","External anal sphincter relaxation occurs via sympathetic stimulation","Colonic peristalsis ceases during defecation","Rectal distension triggers coordinated muscle contraction and sphincter relaxation"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe defecation reflex maintains bowel continence and controlled faecal elimination.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Erectal distension triggers coordinated muscle contraction and sphincter relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E during normal defecation. When faeces enter and the rectum becomes distended (volume approximately 18 mL), stretch receptors initiate the defecation reflex. This involves:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EParasympathetic stimulation causing internal anal sphincter relaxation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVoluntary control of external anal sphincter relaxation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECoordinated contraction of colonic and rectal muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExternal anal sphincter relaxation occurs via sympathetic stimulation\u003C/strong\u003E - The external sphincter is under voluntary somatic control via the pudendal nerve\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInternal anal sphincter remains contracted throughout defecation\u003C/strong\u003E - The internal sphincter must relax via parasympathetic stimulation for defecation to occur\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERectal distension triggers immediate faecal expulsion\u003C/strong\u003E - The external sphincter can maintain continence through voluntary control even when the reflex is triggered\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColonic peristalsis ceases during defecation\u003C/strong\u003E - Colonic peristalsis actually increases during defecation to help propel faeces\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis coordinated reflex ensures controlled elimination while maintaining continence when socially inappropriate.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The internal anal sphincter relaxes via parasympathetic innervation while the external sphincter is under voluntary control.","The defecation reflex involves coordinated contraction of colonic and rectal muscles with relaxation of anal sphincters."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57139"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17224"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57139","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57139"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T08:51:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T08:52:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9914"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71643"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","